race.comment: Tough contest to end the day. BLAKEMORE AVENUE (6) progressive mare who sprinted well fresh when a commanding winner over 1200m at Beaudesert. Gets the right run again and looks set for a big prep. THE TORQUE XPRESS (2) is going nicely through his grades this time in with the two wins from three starts. Picked them up with ease from back in the field when saluting over 1200m at Ipswich. Comes here at his top and gets map favours. Go close. INQUISITOR (3) was rewarded for his consistency when he finished over the top of them at this track and trip last time out. Up slightly in weight and can repeat the effort. OVAL OFFICE (4) game effort first-up from the lengthy break when a fighting on-pace second over 1265m at this track. Will appreciate the weight drop and looks set for a good campaign.
